Nutrition of children suffering from obesity: No breakfast and sausage for dinner
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 weigh more than normal; while 9% of school children are overweight, 5% are obese.
According to the latest study, children suffering from obesity usually come from families leading an unhealthy lifestyle.
We see again the importance of the environment and the behaviors that accompany a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausage appears on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children with normal weight.
More than 19% of children suffering from obesity ate French fries for dinner on the eve of a survey relating to an educational event called Obesity is not an accident.
Moreover, the families of children suffering from obesity do not play sports. This, however, applies to the majority of families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said that their parents find time to play sports at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of last school year and involved nearly 900 elementary school students across Bohemia.
Obesity was not an accident for the second year in a row, with the support of the insurance company Véobecnj zdravotnj pojijovna and Unilever.
To date, more than 12 thousand students of grades 4-8 have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and sufficient exercise are the main determining factors that cause a rapidly growing number of children who suffer from either overweight or obesity.
“For example, only half of the respondents said that they eat five times a day, according to the scheme of breakfast-dinner-lunch-dinner-dinner, and this is one of the indispensable conditions for proper nutrition,” says one of the conclusions of the study.
No lunch and no sausage in the evenings.
Experts warn that even such relative details as the constant time of family breakfast are important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of school children eat breakfast together.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast separately.
The worst finding is that one in ten families doesn’t have breakfast at all.
And yet breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study showed that fried foods are more often consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sugary soft drinks every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children regularly play sports, this figure is reduced by more than half - up to 15% - when it comes to their parents.
Make your own menu.
In another part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the products offered and based on their tastes and preferences.
"Food preferences in Czech children aged 12-15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Their favorite food includes a large number of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
"Of particular concern is the great popularity of sweet soft drinks," the study concludes.
As the main dining dish, the pasta defeated the bird with a small margin.
However, the children showed little interest in legumes, fish and vegetable dishes.
The pursuit of a healthy lifestyle
The study also showed that children are ready to change their eating habits, provided that they are provided with relevant information.
“Many participants in the study’s control group showed a significant shift in preferences toward healthy eating when they filled out a questionnaire after completing a lecture on Obesity is not an accident,” the project said.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sweet soft drinks - more children began to prefer them to just water.
In addition, as the main dish, children were more likely to celebrate poultry and fish, limiting the number of sweet dishes and pastries.
The stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article about trainings for stylists, I lamented the amount of information at the introductory classes.
I had no idea what was going to happen.
Lectures by three experts in the field; tips on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a seminar on how it all works in real life.
Next is more.
The closer we are to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
The training takes place every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, (there are no men on the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
One has a short neck, the other has a boyish figure without proper shapes, another weighs more than normal.
The stylist should know how to visually reduce the wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or add the missing volumes.
We were given advice on how to emphasize the figure of women like Jennifer Lopez, i.e. the owners of a more lush chest and hips and a narrow waist, and not to dress them too provocatively.
For example, if the difference in the volume of the waist and hips is so great that you can not pick up a skirt or trousers, it is worth having at least one thing sewn to order.
You will definitely not regret the money invested, since perfectly seated clothes are priceless.
In a skirt made to order, you will feel much better than in one that constantly moves, rolls, exposes the waist, etc.
Holders of boyish figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with ruches, appliques, embroidery or folds.
Given the abundance of such information and types of figures, I am glad that I have a whole week to realize it.
And yet, I'm afraid that's too much, given the homework we got.
Each participant of the courses had to come up with two outfits for some celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We must take into account their modern appearance, their style in clothes and the type of figure.
I’m going to wear Miranda Kerr, which you might know from Victoria’s Secret advertising campaigns.
I am happy for myself because it is much easier to dress than, say, Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who recently recovered by a ton (please keep in mind that I am exaggerating), or very young Selena Gomez.
We must cut clothes from magazines or find them on the Internet, print and process them using graphic programs.
Mudboard - the so-called result of the work - then reflects our own style and attitude to the graphic image.
It is important to keep in mind the graphic component of the style.
The stylist does not just dress real people, but creates food pages in magazines (based on special instructions, for example, fashionable bags, coats, etc.).
This is what the stylist and designer Mario Kamenik told us about.
But it was only on Sunday.
A stylist needs general knowledge
Saturday's lecture, rich with information about the types of figures, was revived by three guests - specialists in this field.
Stylist, Honza Pokorna; fashion designer, Jakub Polanka; and fashion photographer Ben Rench.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should use this fact.
A good stylist can use one piece of clothing in different ways.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a trench coat can be worn in the usual way, over jeans and T-shirts like a coat; but it can also be worn on a bare body, without fasteners like a dress.
Another possibility is to roll up your sleeves or lift your collar, and the whole image changes completely.
“Play with him,” he said.
In any case, I most appreciated the following advice: “For your work, you must know the rules perfectly.”
Then you can start to break them," Yakub told us.
Here I finally understood why we cram all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, whereas in fashion magazines we often see something completely different.
Not to mention fashion shows.
From Ben, the photographer, I learned that the stylist should have more outfit options than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a fashion review of ten pages (equivalent to ten outfits), I must be ready to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that in the picture, the garment often looks and works in combination with others in a completely different way than in reality.
We have to keep this in mind when we create an image.
Honza Pokorna confirmed that often image and style are half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who doesn’t have amazing vocals, but her image and marketing have turned her into a world star.
The attitude towards the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even famous people often consider it superfluous (and believe that it is enough to be an expert in something, and how they look - a second time).
And if someone finally lets us create their style, we should expect them to name us a different (less) size than the one they really wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids wrote anything about the fact that some celebrity got fat / lost weight, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario emphasized that it is not enough for a stylist to understand fashion and be able to pick up an outfit.
Our job is mainly to communicate with the people we dress; so it’s important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to evaluate people, not to condone them and hold their opinion.
“If a manager asks you to look at her clothes and add some beautiful things, you can’t throw away her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are terrible.”
“Find at least a few things that you can praise, and advise what you can wear with them,” says Mario.
He also showed us exactly what a work bag should hold.
This is a bag that you tie around the waist to wear everything you need.
In addition to obvious things such as scissors, sticky roller or English pins, it should be nylon thread (stylists use it when shooting some items, such as bags or hats), special clips to fasten the fabric on the back in case the clothes are too large (bumps and similar items are prohibited as they spoil the clothes) or a sewing set.
In order to distract from lectures and get some practical experience, we learned how to properly make linings on the soles of shoes.
Even while filming in a studio where the floor is smooth, the soles can get damaged - not to mention shooting outdoors.
And here we are, sticking.
You don’t have to touch the shoes with scissors to not spoil them.
It requires real skill.
I was pleased that Mario praised my work.
These skills did not appeal to me.
This is only part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend courses.
I’m starting to realize that being a professional stylist isn’t so easy no matter what you say.
V Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Overview
What was supposed to be a carefree walk turned into a routine morning commute due to a series of completely inappropriate and careless mistakes.
Ambitions have been met to some extent, but that doesn’t matter because no one clearly wanted to do the extra work.
Before the release of the new version with the subtitle "Escape" there were high hopes.
It was expected to shift the previous Need For Speed series in a new direction; demo versions indicated that the game would take a worthy place in the genre of racing games.
We were curious to see the parts of the game where the main character gets out of the car and runs.
As is often the case with NFS, in the end, a lot of things are different from what we expected.
The game is a pretty good arcade race, but the overall impression is spoiled by several unnecessary mistakes that have been present in this series of games for several years.
So, in reality, this is not a mistake, but a manifestation of the inexplicable laziness of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You become part of the story, the main character of which, Jack, solves some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You get in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get to New York first.
This idea has some interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race takes its own route, individual stages take place in a diverse and interesting environment.
There is no feeling that the same thing happens in the game all the time.
Despite the fact that the graphics are at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some tracks are pleasant to look at.
And yet the game does not cause strong emotions.
Although driving through the desert, in the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the race from time to time revives an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert you fall into a sandstorm, significantly reducing visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to fall under the avalanche.
Individual races are pretty well-ordered.
There are only a few varieties, but that’s enough.
For a while, you try to overtake a few opponents (essentially a normal race); then you try to improve time (a standard stopwatch race); or you compete against one opponent.
Among other things, from time to time you come across the police, which further complicates your task.
The components outside the car are new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
It's no big deal.
Although it is surprising that these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (only three to be exact).
In fact, it turns out to be good for the game because it’s a property that doesn’t get bored; given all of the above, it’s one of the things that makes the game more entertaining.
The racing model follows in the footsteps of previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you are looking for an imitation of real life, you will have to look elsewhere.
And yet, this driving model is very suitable for dynamic racing, although better options can be found on the market.
So far, it's very good.
However, after a while, problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not as good.
From such a game you do not expect difficult transformations and collisions, but if you have no idea before the collision with the object, how your car will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, by overtaking or passing cars in a dense stream, you sometimes touch another car slightly. And yet, sometimes in a practically similar situation, your car begins to unwind wildly.
Or smashed to shreds.
It’s not that important thanks to the restart system, but it’s enough to spoil the fun.
Restarts are designed so that if you crash or get far away from the track, the game returns you to the point where it was interrupted.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them all, you’ll have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful in case something doesn’t work out, but you can’t completely rely on it.
Sometimes restarts are not enough, and you have to memorize a separate section of the race by heart.
An important disadvantage of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to be done in a certain way, otherwise you just won’t fit in.
In other cases, you meet civilian cars at a specific location in the same configuration, regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds early or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see your opponent easily drive between two cars moving in the opposite direction, whereas when you find yourself there, the cars are already positioned so that you either need to go around them or lose speed.
It doesn’t matter when you find yourself next to them; everything is arranged in such a way that the situation always happens just in front of your nose.
Competitors have other advantages.
During the game, you find several places where, regardless of time, the same opponent overtakes you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on a long bridge where you drive in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent must stand in front of you no matter what.
The fact is that when he rides in front of you, he worsens your view, which leads to one or more accidents at this site.
One can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and adrenaline-filled, but it is so obvious that it quickly begins to cause irritation.
It’s a shame because despite the simple driving model, the game is entertaining and sometimes so eventful that you don’t have time to pay attention to what’s going on around you.
It doesn’t matter what makes you bored — a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races, or anything else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
You need to track gas stations along the way, because it is on them that your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases, the one that you already have is quite enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars for straight stretches of highway; and exotic super-sports cars for technical driving, for example, along curved mountain slopes.
The main story mode is closely related to the challenge mode; these are races on individual sites that you will learn during the game.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and points common to challenges and story modes.
Many features are available to get a higher level of driving: from machines to profile data.
In addition, the profile is associated with the online Autolog function, which, among other things, compares the results you have achieved with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here is another drawback that is difficult to understand; this is an example from the last race in sequence.
You and your car get into the subway tunnel (we’ll assume it is) where you race on the rails in the dark (we’ll assume it is).
Your speedometer shows the numbers from 150 to 200 km/h (let’s assume that this is the case) when suddenly a subway train comes on you from behind, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
For several days, our editorial board discussed whether no one really thought for a second during the creation of the game, or its creators really consider us such fools.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video sequence is mostly pleasant, sometimes even stunning.
Although it is a pity that in some critical moments the quality of recording, sometimes quite strongly, decreases.
This is especially true for events with a large number of participants, where a good record would not help you much either.
The sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the amateur.
To please the widest possible youth audience, the soundtrack 'entered compositions from different styles'; but hardly many people will buy the game because of its music.
Need for Speed: Escape is pretty messy.
If the game were to avoid obviously unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of NFS in the last few years.
Anyway, the game leaves a feeling of incompleteness.
Of course, this is a good entertainment, but be prepared for the fact that the flaws will blind you like an airport spotlight.
Choirs of Charles University will perform at the concert "Students in Velvet"
For the third year in a row, Festa Academia offers to combine International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical event.
He will present about twenty school and university choirs.
The main event of the festival is two concerts, which will be held on November 17.
"Karlov University takes active part in festival".
"The participating choirs include the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities; Vaclav Gample, the rector, will join the committee," said Jakub Chalun, head of the organizing committee.
The culmination will be a free public concert of school choirs, which will take place at 2 p.m. on November 17 at the square in front of the National Technical Library in Deivica.
The work "Jazz Mass", an essay by the famous Czech jazzman, Karel Ruzhychki, is also included in the program.
In the evening, a concert "Students in Velvet" will be held in the official National House in Vinogradi, with the participation of university choirs, including the choirs of Charles University.
The goal of Festa Academica is to celebrate International Student Day and to celebrate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution; to present the highest quality choral music to the public and to develop creative interaction among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech choirs in cooperation with Johannes Kepler High School.
The whole event is held with the assistance of Boguslav Svoboda, Lord Mayor of Prague, and Vaclav Gampla, Rector of Charles University.
The festival will be held from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers both official concerts, as well as numerous musical meetings, students’ happenings, daytime performances, etc.
For more information, please visit the festival website: www.festaacademica.cz
Ambassador to the EU Vicenova:
The Czechs have a reputation of detractors and skeptics against the euro.
"The Lisbon Treaty has caused significant differences between individual organizations."
"I didn't expect such a brutal war."
“It will take five or six years before the situation somehow stabilizes, calms down and all players get used to their new roles,” EU Ambassador Milena Vitsenova rigidly began her lecture at the Faculty of Law.
She proved how she adhered to her motto “Clearly and openly about Europe” in the first part of her lecture, where she described the individual institutions of the EU and the relationship between them so simply and clearly that many lecturers from the Faculty of Law of the KU would envy.
Moreover, Vicenova praised the work of the new permanent President of the European Council, Herman Van Rompuy:
“At first, critics said he was an ordinary gray office mouse that couldn’t perform any role; I have to say everyone was amazed at how well he handled his role.”
“He is a person who can listen to twenty-seven participating countries at the same time, communicate with them perfectly and who has a clear idea of which direction the EU needs to develop.”
She explained her new position as a representative on foreign and security affairs as an answer to the question: "Who is the European Union? What number do I need to call?"; i.e. as an important step towards unification and greater transparency of the Union's policy towards countries such as China or India.
No one is going to ban our cheeses.
Vicenova further focused on the program, which is key for the EU in the past, present and near future.
She called the successful presidency of the Czech Republic in the year before.
The Czechs were dealing with an impending financial crisis; they overcame this crisis and organized the Eastern Partnership Summit.
She said that the resignation of the government at that time was a negative phenomenon that caused considerable damage to the Czech Republic.
Czechs are very busy in the EU.
As the Ambassador said, both the presidency and the subsequent financial crisis have caused the ongoing ferment.
In addition, it is necessary to adopt a new seven-year EU budget, which is very difficult, given the current crisis.
Whether the budget will be meager and economical, which areas will be preferred; which countries will receive more support and which will receive less; all these issues are in the upcoming program.
The ambassador recalled the key slogans that she brought to Brussels: “About Europe, Intelligible Language”.
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words and jargon that no one understands.
How can citizens understand that in Brussels people are not trying to sell curves or round cucumbers, bananas of different sizes, or that someone is going to ban our varieties of cheese?
It is also going to make better use of the EU environment and attract more Czechs to European organizations.
Multi-speed Europe is our future
The ambassador claims that the Czechs are considered Euro-skeptics; as well as people who note the negative rather than the positive aspects of things.
She wants more Czech representatives to be involved in European organizations.
She believes that several factors are to blame: for example, the modesty of our candidates and their inability to write motivational letters; at the same time with little support from the Czech side.
Along with the successful chairmanship of the Czech Republic, she noted the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when I meet someone from Poland and Hungary, and a Slovak joins us, the Frenchman next to me says: 'Hey, what about the meeting, the Visegrad group again?' and he is not even a little happy about it.
In the future, the Union expects mostly new strict rules for the budget policy of the member states.
Compared with the new European Federation, she considers the idea of a two-speed, if not multi-speed Europe more realistic.
“We have countries both inside and outside the eurozone.”
"We have the Schengen area, and we already have an institution of enhanced cooperation."
“For the first time, it was said that countries that want to unite, while those that do not want to, can stay away.”
“The number of such institutions will grow; it will be a truly two-speed Europe,” expects Vicenova.
In this regard, she stressed the role of both the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuy in promoting the rule that all EU-wide issues should be discussed by all member states, not just those in the Eurozone.
Brand history:
IBM is entering the second century of its existence.
If someone wants to find the word that best expresses the IMB strategy, the closest is likely to be “durable.”
For the general public, IBM is a symbol of the technological revolution; the company is considered very modern, although it was founded more than a hundred years ago.
The company's longevity was laid down by its first boss, dreamer Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He believed in his motto that many of the world’s problems could be easily solved if people wanted to think.
His slogan "Think!" thus became the stamp around which the life of the future giant unfolded (as well as the name of his internal magazine, which IMB began to publish in 1935).
Moreover, it was the basis of the corporate culture that Watson carefully built.
“For us at IBM, long-term thinking means constant movement toward the future.
IBM survived and prospered for a hundred years because it remained true to its original values, although it was not afraid to change everything around it.
In our first hundred years, it has enabled us to transform technology, business and company.
In the second hundred years, we hope to achieve even more,” says the current head of the company, Samuel J. Palmizano, on the occasion of the anniversary.
Complex system
In the 1930s, Watson approached the issue of employee care in the same way that Batja in the Czech Republic - IMB employees were among the first American employees with paid leave, employer insurance, elegant uniforms, and a complex bonus system for top inventors and entrepreneurs.
IBM’s long-term relationship with consumers is similarly advanced.
From the very beginning, the company found brilliant applications for talented people. It was one of the first global companies to eliminate all discrimination, which provided it with an excellent choice.
Agrees with the anti-discrimination strategy and the current plan, according to which a woman, Virginia Rometty, will succeed Palmisano next year.
She has worked at IBM for thirty years; she is currently Director of Sales, Marketing and Development.
