An official delegation led by Uruguayan President Jose Mujica and consisting of several ministers and businessmen will arrive in Mexico on Tuesday to expand trade between the two countries and to begin talks on the region's political problems.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with his Mexican counterpart, Felipe Calderon, the most important point of the extensive plan of meetings with political, commercial authorities and meetings with the community of Uruguayans living in Mexico, according to a schedule published by the Uruguayan leadership.
