The international community, led by Washington, is now pressuring Abuja to address the challenges posed by Boko Haram.
The fact is that the Nigerian authorities have traditionally viewed this group as a community of enlightened people of no interest.
Rapid success
Founded in 2002 in Maidiguri at the mosque, school and under Imam fundamentalist Mohammed Yusuf, Boko Haram - which means "Western education is a sin" - preaches the establishment of an Islamic emirate in the Muslim north of Nigeria.
In this poor region, the organization has achieved rapid success.
